<p>Uruguay’s senate passed a law on Wednesday decriminalizing euthanasia, making the country the first in Latin America to allow it through legislation [firstpost.com#1][france24.com#1][apnews.com#1]. The measure permits seriously ill patients to request medical assistance to end their lives under a new “dignified death” framework [firstpost.com#1][lemonde.fr#1]. It cleared its final hurdle with 20 of 31 senators voting in favor after a years-long debate that drew opposition from the Catholic Church [thehindu.com#1][dw.com#1][lemonde.fr#1]. Elsewhere in the region, Colombia and Ecuador had decriminalized euthanasia through Supreme Court decisions, highlighting Uruguay’s legislative route [france24.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/29Ghu8QZ3X2qxNLwDBY4sjUKQwBzD-_TwqqIav546A--n7ILnrOeMb4wVRePAdiCB0BgAixMC9DOHUsU5gxA4v0XEDYg5diQBK2xBgd3o_DTgAmqho0uI5DdwBimEN0teX5u35E4pG1xwirZ2N-o_FqHcsX7PC-DIlf4FphWk6PWHD4wMqKizXK7HZ6qHpeCjiEM' alt='Uruguay’s Legislative Palace in Montevideo on October 15, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Regional backdrop: Uruguay is the first in predominantly Catholic Latin America to allow euthanasia by legislation, distinguishing it within the region [france24.com#1].</li><li>Legislative path: The proposal advanced in fits and starts over the last five years before clearing the senate [thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Assisted suicide: Reports describe the reform as legalizing assisted suicide alongside euthanasia, placing Uruguay among the first in Latin America to permit it [lemonde.fr#1][ndtv.com#1].</li><li>Different routes: Colombia and Ecuador reached decriminalization via Supreme Court rulings rather than parliamentary votes, underscoring varied legal pathways in the region [france24.com#1].</li><li>Policy tradition: Observers note Uruguay’s long history of socially liberal laws, providing context for this end-of-life legislation [straitstimes.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Catholic Church: The Church opposed the euthanasia law during the years-long debate. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/uruguay-passes-law-legalizing-euthanasia/a-74376809'>DW</a>)</li><li>Supporters in senate: Backers framed the measure as a “Dignified Death” law following a decade-long debate. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/16/uruguay-passes-law-to-legalize-euthanasia_6746476_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/uruguay-becomes-first-south-american-nation-to-legalise-euthanasia-as-senate-passes-the-law-13942552.html'>Uruguay becomes first South American nation to legalise euthanasia as senate passes the law</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20251016-uruguay-legalizes-euthanasia'>In regional first, Uruguay passes law allowing euthanasia</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/uruguay-passes-law-legalizing-euthanasia/a-74376809'>Uruguay passes law legalizing euthanasia</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/16/uruguay-passes-law-to-legalize-euthanasia_6746476_4.html'>Uruguay passes law to legalize euthanasia</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/uruguay-legalises-euthanasia'>Uruguay legalises euthanasia</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/uruguay-euthanasia-latin-america-uruguay-becomes-first-latin-american-country-to-legalise-euthanasia-9464030#publisher=newsstand'>Uruguay Becomes First Latin American Country To Legalise Euthanasia</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/in-a-regional-first-uruguay-passes-law-allowing-euthanasia/article70169866.ece'>In a regional first, Uruguay passes law allowing euthanasia</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://apnews.com/article/uruguay-euthanasia-law-076a2f4d2ba5ce990e65ac4dd4798d49'>Uruguay becomes the first country in Latin America to decriminalise euthanasia vi